*****************************
*    Additional Software    *
*****************************

Further reading: https://wiki.archlinux.org/index.php/List_of_applications
You can use "pac" instead of "sudo pacman"
Check out full list of aliases in ~/.bashrc file
Here is a list of useful software that you may wish to install:

All commands to type into terminal are written after $ sign.
Open up terminal and run following commands:

# Libre Office
$ pac libreoffice

# GIMP aka GNU Image Manipulation Program (Advanced Photo Editor)
$ pac gimp

# GNOME Calendar (Time Managing Software)
$ pac gnome-calendar

# Rclone file cloner into Google Drive, Dropbox, etc.
$ pac rclone

# RSS reader
$ pac quiterss

# PAMAC (GUI Package Manager)
$ yay -S pamac-aur

# Calibre, E-book reader and file converter 
$ pac calibre

# Network Monitor/Scanner
$ pac nmap

# Arduino IDE
$ pac arduino


******************
* For developers *
******************

# Code::Blocks C/C++
$ pac codeblocks

# Eclipse Java EE
$ pac eclipse-jee

# Eclipse Java
$ pac eclipse-java

# Eclipse C/C++
$ pac eclipse-cpp

# Eclipse PHP
$ pac eclipse-php

# Eclipse JavaScript and Web
$ pac eclipse-javascript

# Netbeans Python, Java, Ruby, etc.
$ pac netbeans

# PyCharm Python
$ pac pycharm-community-edition

# Spyder Python2
$ pac spyder2

# Spyder Python3
$ pac spyder3

# IntelliJ Java
$ pac intellij-idea-community-edition

# JSON reading tool
$ wget https://github.com/antonmedv/fx/releases/download/14.0.1/fx-linux.zip
$ unzip fx-linux.zip
$ sudo mv fx-linux /usr/local/bin/fx
